node.text: The road that leads to Roger W. Smith's remote workshop is not so different from the one that leads to Philippe Dufour’s. But while the Swiss can blame tradition for their isolation, this Brit's exile appears to be self-imposed. For the full story, go to https://www.hodinkee.com/articles/episode-1-roger-w-smith

node.text: It’s not often you get to be in the presence of true greatness. And I know on this site we tend to talk up how wonderful this watch is or how revelatory that watch is. We even, at at times, say things like “this is a once-in-a-lifetime” chance to see this or that. And we mean it when we say it, but we are speaking in relative terms, because we are, after all, talking about watches. But today, I'll speak in far more literal terms, because in this special episode of Talking Watches I talk to an actual living legend. In fact, just a few weeks ago in Palm Beach, Florida, I had the honor of sitting down with a man who is the very best in the world at something – someone who remains at the pinnacle of his sport, though his reign ended decades ago. I'm talking about Jack Nicklaus. Yes, the Jack Nicklaus. For the full story, go to https://www.hodinkee.com/articles/talking-watches-with-jack-nicklaus

node.text:
"And for our next trick, watch as we make the power reserve indicator disappear (Well, from the dial at least)." - Grand Seiko. 
If you haven't read @jackjforster take on the new G.S. SLGA008 and SLGA007, here's some of what you need to know:
The first new 9RA2 watch is the Grand Seiko Heritage Collection Seiko 140th Anniversary Limited Edition "Tree Rings" (SLGA008), featuring a rose gold case and  a limited production run of 140 pieces.
The second is the limited edition Grand Seiko Heritage Collection Seiko 140th Anniversary "Minamo Lake Suwa" (SLGA007) which features  a wave-patterned blue dial. The release is limited to 2021 pieces. 

More pics, descriptions and pricing live on Hodinkee.

node.text: "Honoring a 1957 series of prototypes created by Bulova for the U.S. Navy based around the ​​MIL-SHIPS-W-2181 mil-spec contract for early military frogmen, the Bulova MIL-SHIPS Reissue revives a rare bird that today's Bulova organization wasn't even aware existed. It was the perseverance of a single collector, fascinated by the history of military dive watches, who brought the watch to the company's attention and helped them bring it back to life today." @watchesbylogan has more at the link in bio.

node.text: From the archives. A DoE scientist with an Omega Seamaster on his wrist is soaking concrete in a monomer plastic, and then exposing it to gamma radiation to polymerize the plastic in the small cavities of the concrete. Not entirely sure what all that means, but something tells me @jackjforster might. Be sure to share your archival photos with the hashtag #watchthearchives and click the link in bio to see @cole_pennington original article.
